        <abstract>
            <p>CD interested in hybrid sterility and encloses his preliminary MS. Outlines experiments to test for existence of sterility in breeds of poultry and pigeons.</p> 
<p>Experiments on dimorphism have led him to change in part his opinion as given in <hi rend="italic">Origin</hi>, and he is now asking pigeon and poultry fanciers for any examples of special selective sterility [i.e., a particular pair are sterile when crossed, but each individual is fertile with others] and hopes to investigate its inheritance.</p> 
        </abstract>
